### Health check
GET http://localhost:8000/health


### 1. Submit a happy-path job
POST http://localhost:8000/jobs
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: test-happy-2

{
  "manuscript": "ALICE: It was a dark and stormy night.\nBOB: Are you absolutely certain about that?\nALICE: Yes, the thunder shook the windows.\nNARRATOR: And so it began."
}


### 2. Poll job status (replace JOB_ID with id from above response)
GET http://localhost:8000/jobs/JOB_ID


### 3. Idempotency — same key, different text → should return SAME job_id as request 1
POST http://localhost:8000/jobs
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: test-happy-1

{
  "manuscript": "ALICE: This is different text but same idempotency key."
}


### 4. Poison pill — should reach FAILED, message goes to parse.dlq
POST http://localhost:8000/jobs
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: test-poison-1

{
  "manuscript": "ALICE: This manuscript contains POISON and should fail.\nBOB: It will never reach TTS."
}


### 5. Poll poison job status (replace POISON_JOB_ID)
GET http://localhost:8000/jobs/POISON_JOB_ID


### 6. Semaphore burst — submit 3 jobs at once (run all 3 quickly back to back)
POST http://localhost:8000/jobs
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: test-burst-1

{
  "manuscript": "ALICE: Burst job one unique line abc123.\nBOB: Second unique line xyz456."
}

###
POST http://localhost:8000/jobs
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: test-burst-2

{
  "manuscript": "ALICE: Burst job two unique line def456.\nBOB: Second unique line uvw789."
}

